<plot>The film arranges a series of interconnected vignettes taken from an in-depth interview with Susan Neiman, author of the influential book Evil in Modern Thought. She explains how the great modern philosophers obsessed over and approached the problem of evil as the world developed between the Lisbon Earthquake of 1755 through the discovery of Auschwitz. Neiman then offers a discussion on the interplay between terrorism and the Bush Administration, that offers profound insight into the post September 11th world.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?184793</url></doc>
